strings.Value: "Are you participating in the debates too?"
"Why do you have those jerboas there?"
"It's like a spell was cast over my friend when he read the rules. Did anything like that happen to you?"
"So what do you want to ask the Host if you win?"
{n}A little kobold raises his little snout at you.{/n} "Greetingsss!"
{n}The kobold lowers his head.{/n} "Fey sssay: need three. I no three. I no friendsss. Wanted go very much, caught thisss jump mice. Now we are three! Partisssipate!"
"I don't read. Gnome help me. Read for me. Aloud. But then ssscream. I ssscared!"
"Amazing! We'll be competing against the inarticulate kin of unforgettable Tartuk!"
"What is this I hear?! A kobold, a fellow tribesman of unforgettable Tartuk – damn his tentacles – has decided to participate in the debates!"
"AMAZING! Even the inarticulate kin of UNFORGETTABLE TARTUK are here!"
{n}The jerboas turn their heads to Jubilost and hiss in indignation, and the kobold shivers.{/n} "You ssscream ssscary. Another gnome ssscream ssscary too. Angry gnome, I ssscare."
{n}The kobold looks at Jubilost with interest.{/n} "Huge frog! You ssspeak? Can me mount you? I feed you antsss, clean you ssskin. I am rider!"
"In the list of all the job offers I've ever received, that will be honorably placed in the 'I'm ready to cry' section."
"Kobold! Partisssipate!" {n}The little kobold is very proud of himself.{/n}
